cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for recognizing human skin in images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for skin detection, which makes it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes a new algorithm for skin detection, which involves the use of color models, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques, which makes it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the recognition of skin-colored pixels and regions in images, which makes it relevant to cs.GR (Graphics).
